title: Gents Race 7.0
description:
The BikeIowa.com Cycling Team would like to request the presence of YOU and 4 teammates for the Gents Race 7.0 on April 1st 2017.
Stay tuned... We'll pick another worthy charity this year.

This race is insured as a USAC Gran Fondo race. No license required.

This will be the 7th year of the Gents race and we expect 2017 to bigger than last year.

By the numbers...
2016 - 64 teams signed up. 18 finished - WINDY!
2015 - 64 teams signed up. 45 finished
2014 - 45 teams signed up. 33 finished
2013 - 37 teams signed up. 24 finished
2012 - 30 teams signed up. 22 finished
2011 - 15 teams signed up. 13 finished

START LOCATION - NITE HAWK BAR AND GRILL
START TIME - 8AM, at NITE HAWK BAR AND GRILL

FINISH - at NITE HAWK BAR AND GRILL
CUTOFF - 3PM
POST-PARTY -  AT NITE HAWK BAR AND GRILL!!!!


UPDATES
Jan 18th - Event Posted


WHAT IS A GENTS RACE?
Glad you asked!  To directly quote the folks at Rapha that started the whole concept (and that we’ve blatantly stolen it from): ‘I sold it to the racers as an unsupported, unsanctioned, unmarshalled, five-rider team time trial meets alley-cat, meets ‘Cannonball Run’…….

So there you have it. 5 teammates (friends), racing for nothing more than pride over the roads surrounding Slater, Iowa. 65 (or so) miles of gravel.

Winners get nothing but pride and high-fives.

No money to enter, no money to win.

It will be fun.



RULES?
Yes:  There are a few rules...

    No cheating. No working with/drafting off of other teams. All teammates must stay together at all times. No bad attitudes. No outside support. Be Gentlemen (or ladies).

    To make it interesting teams will be staged according to your team's potential. If you have a fast team then you will be one of the last teams to start the race. For instance - first team left the starting line last year at 8am sharp while the last team left at 9:30am. The race is a time handicapped race. It makes for a very interesting finish.

    Remember, there WILL be a staggered start for each team. First team goes off at 8AM, with each remaining team rolling out at equally spaced intervals yet to be determined.

    You are responsible for YOU-you are doing this event at YOUR risk. For you, by you. Take care of yourself. Ride smart. Roads will be open to traffic. Dogs will come say hello. Miles will add up. NO neutral support. NO sag wagon. NO power food sponsorship. Again, you are doing this BY CHOICE.

    There will be a mandatory checkpoint at or around the race halfway point. Here, you will also have access to your drop bag (one per team).

    Your TEAM CAPTAIN will register the complete team below. We are shutting it down at midnight on March XX 2016. You must be registered by then or no gents for you. (Date coming soon)

    Teams can be comprised of all males, all females or a mix of both.

    All staging handicaps are final. Our team of Nerf-ball engineers have devised a special algorithm to ensure every team has the correct handicap.

    Time penalties will occur for any changes to your roster AFTER registration closes. No exceptions. 



TEAMS
I have a Team of 5.  Cool - Register below.

I have a Team but need one or more person.  Almost there - You can request a teammate via our Facebook page.

I am looking for a Team.  Sure Thang.- You can put you name out via our Facebook page.



COMMUNICATION
The ONLY correspondence going out to your team will go to your TEAM CAPTAIN, it’s THEIR responsibility to relay information to YOU.
 
General information and updates about The Gents Race can always be found right here (See the updates section).

We will send you your assigned start time and route on or around March 29th.

Questions, concerns or issues? We’re here to help.

Rob (robsversteegh@gmail.com)
Kyle (ksedore@gmail.com
Bruce (bhreese73@gmail.com)

title: Spooky Cross
description: Join Zealous Racing  Oct. 28th and 29th for a spooktacular weekend of cyclocross benefitting JDRF!
course: Course consists of great flow, challenging off-cambers, hills, single-track and more!  The Architect has been hard at work this year designing a mix of all of your favorites features to make a for a challenging and fun weekend of cross!
registration: Pre-Registration - Save $10! Pre-register with USA Cycling for $25(www.usacycling.org)
notes:
Staging of races will be based on USAC ranking score for pre-registered riders, and on first come basis for day for race day registrants.  In the event of low rider turnout, promoter reserves the right to cancel/combine events and prize lists as necessary, or to award prizes to only the top half of each category.
Masters Women may compete in Men's Masters Race's as follows: Category 1 and 2 Master's Women may enter Men's events for riders up to 10 years above their racing ages; Category 3 and 4 Master's Women may enter Men's events up to 20 years above their racing ages.
directions: From I-80, take Exit 143(1st Ave. N) South to 8th St. SW.  Take a right onto 8th St. SW(Kum&Go on corner).  Head West on 8th St. SW until Venbury Drive.  Take a left on Venbury Drive and head South(past Altoona Fire Station) to the Altoona Aquatic Center Parking Lot which will be on your left hand side.

title: Iowa State Cyclocross Championships
description: Held under USAC Permit 2017-3002.  All USAC rules apply.  Helmets must be worn at all times.
course: Contact -- Race day contact, Paul Jensen -- (515) 868-8506
registration:
PRE-REGISTRATION -- Pre-registration will be available via USA Cycling (http://www.usacycling.org). Preregistration will be $25 ($10 saving compared to race day registration) and includes a FREE Iowa Cyclocross State Championship T-shirt AVAILABLE FOR PRE-ORDER THROUGH NOVEMBER 18TH AT MIDNIGHT. 

RACE DAY REGISTRATION -- Registration opens at 9:00am and closes 15 minutes prior to each race. Race day registration will be $35 for all riders (except Juniors which will still be Free). Riders will receive $10 off their second race registration the same day.
notes:
STAGING -- Staging will start with pre-registered riders in order by their USAC ranking http:// www.usacycling.org/events/rr.php) as of Nov 23rd. Then by same-day registered riders in the order of their registration. Each time-slot will be staged as a single group with no gaps for medal categories. 

MEDALS -- State medals will be awarded to the top three annually Iowa licensed riders in each of the following categories: Junior Girls/Boys 10-13, Junior Girls/Boys 14-18. Senior Men/Women in the following categories: Masters 35-44, Masters 45-54, Masters 55+, Category 4/5, Category 3, Category 1/2. 

***PLEASE READ***In the event of low rider turnout,the organizers reserve the right to cancel/combine events and prize lists as necessary.  Prizes will be awarded to only the top half of each category.
directions: From I-80 take 1st Ave. (exit 143) south to Advetureland Dr., west approximately one mile to 17th Ave. NW, south to 4th St. SW, east to 15th Ave. SW, south to Lions Park.
